matchDeal(address,bytes32[],bytes32[][][.details: Match Deal with Compute Units provided.There should be `bytes32[][] calldata peers` as well, but it is not supported by subgraph codegen.Ref to https://github.com/graphprotocol/graph-tooling/issues/342.

params.computeUnits: : Compute Units per offer id (3D array: provider -> peer -> CU) to match with.
params.offers: : Offers array that represents offers in computeUnits 3D array.

reportWorkerActivated(bytes32,bytes32,by.details: Report that a worker is activated, only throws event

matchDeal(address,bytes32[],bytes32[][][.notice: Match deal with offers and compute units (peers checks through compute units).It validates provided CUs and silently ignore unvalidated ones on checking:- deal.maxWorkersPerProvider and silently ignore other CUs out of this limit.- Offer, or Peer not allowed to match (deal.isProviderAllowed, allowed prices, paymentToken, effectors)- Compute Unit (CU): Active CC status, also note, protocol does not allow more than one CU per peerfor the same Deal. But, when deal consists of whitelisted provider - CUs of this Providercould be matched without even CC.TODO: consolidate workaround: when it comes to check CC status, on wrong status the whole transactionwill be failed instead of to be silenced.This method is mirrored in ts-client/src/dealMatcherClient/dealMatcherClient.ts.

devdoc.details: Market contract is responsible for managing the deals and offers

matchDeal(address,bytes32[],bytes32[][][.details: Match Deal with Compute Units provided.There should be `bytes32[][] calldata peers` as well, but it is not supported by subgraph codegen.Ref to https://github.com/graphprotocol/graph-tooling/issues/342.

params.computeUnits: : Compute Units per offer id (3D array: provider -> peer -> CU) to match with.
params.offers: : Offers array that represents offers in computeUnits 3D array.

reportWorkerActivated(bytes32,bytes32,by.details: Report that a worker is activated, only throws event

ComputeUnitsMatched(bytes32,address,byte.details: Emitted when a deal is matched with a compute unit

params.appCID: The app cid of the deal
params.onchainWorkerId: onchain worker id, for use in tools that interact with chain
params.peerId: The peer id of the deal

ComputeUnitsRemovedFromDeal(bytes32,addr.details: Emitted when a compute unit removed from a peer

params.cuIds: The list of compute unit ids

WorkerActivated(bytes32,address,bytes32,.details: Emitted when a worker is activated

MinWorkersNotMatched(uint256).details: Throws if the min workers of the deal is not matched

params._minWorkers: The min workers of the deal
